Spanish Cities Owe $686 Million in Energy Bills, El Mundo Reports

-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 
2011-10-20T07:04:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/spain-cities-owe-500-million-euro-in-energy-bills-el-mundo-says.html
Spanish power companies have asked
their trade association Unesa for the first time to calculate
the total owed in unpaid electricity bills by Spanish town
halls,  El Mundo  reported, citing unidentified people from Unesa.  For the three largest,  Iberdrola SA (IBE) ,  Endesa SA (ELE)  and  Gas
Natural SDG SA (GAS) , unpaid bills amount to 500 million euros ($686
million), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Angeline Benoit in Madrid at 
 abenoit4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net  